Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-brown; cream slip. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 91, 5, most probably, despite the mu. Name Klearchos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0160.33.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0746)
